    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="493"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.023/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">E. M. House</persName> to
                        Brigadier General <persName type="to">C. H. McKinstry</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-04">December 4,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear General McKinstry</hi>: The President having
                    requested me to set in motion some machinery to obtain for the use of the
                    American Delegation at the Peace Conference some valuation of damages done by
                    the Germans in the invaded parts of France and Belgium, I have requested General
                    Pershing to assign to me an officer, whose duties would be to conduct this
                    work.</p>
                <p>General Pershing having assigned you to me for this purpose and you having
                    reported to me and conferred with me, I trust that you will now proceed with
                    this work, consulting with French and Belgian officials as occasions
                    require.</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. M. House</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
